<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She never fails to turn heads when it comes to her sense of style.</p>

<p>And Kelly Brook cut a chic figure as she arrived at Global Studios to present her Heart radio show on Thursday.</p>

<p>The presenter, 40, showcased her sartorial prowess in a long, multi-coloured cardigan with a detailed print and dark jeans. </p>

<p>Looking good: Kelly Brook, 40, cut a chic figure as she arrived at Global Studios to present her Heart radio show on Thursday</p>

<p>The former glamour model also wore a black T-shirt for the day while she added height to her frame with a pair of boots. </p>

<p>Kelly also sported a cream hat while she let her brunette locks fall loose down her shoulders.</p>

<p>The beauty completed her look for the day with a simple gold necklace as she arrived for work.</p>

<p>Kelly was clearly in a good mood as she laughed and joked with two on-duty officers before she made her way inside.  </p>

<p>Fashion: The presenter showcased her sartorial prowess in a long, multi-coloured cardigan with a detailed print and dark jeans</p>

<p>Outfit: The former glamour model also wore a black T-shirt for the day while she added height to her frame with a pair of boots</p>

<p>Casual: Kelly also sported a cream hat while she let her brunette locks fall loose down her shoulders</p>

<p>Kelly's stylish display comes as she admitted she's 'not worried' about her 'weight creeping up'.</p>

<p>She also declared 'diets shouldn't be about deprivation', after revealing she shed a whopping two stone in March.</p>

<p>While she has been keeping busy by exercising at home, her diet consists of 'healthy, low-calorie meals' with sweet treats such as popcorn and homemade fruit lollies.</p>

<p>Banter: Kelly was clearly in a good mood as she laughed and joked with two on-duty officers before she made her way inside</p>

<p>Radiant: The beauty completed her look for the day with a simple gold necklace as she arrived for work</p>

<p>The media personality has been candid about her weight fluctuating, with the bombshell slimming down to a size 10-12 after going to a size 16.</p>

<p>On her current figure, she told new! magazine: 'I'm a real foodie and enjoy cooking. I wasn't surprised at all to see my weight creep up a little over the last few weeks.</p>

<p>'[I've gained] a few pounds, but I'm not worried. I know I can lean on the SlimFast 3.2.1. Plan to deal with my weight loss ups and downs, so I can get back on track.</p>

<p>'It's easy and it works. Diets shouldn't be about deprivation - they need to be sustainable after all.'</p>

